The youth of Scenery Park organised the vigil to remember their peers who died over the weekend. eNCA's Aviwe Mtila reports. #DStv403 EAST LONDON - Pastors attending the night vigil for 21 teenagers who died at the Enyobeni tavern are calling for calm. The youth of Scenery Park organised the vigil to remember their peers who died over the weekend. READ: Enyobeni Tavern owner criminally charged The circumstances leading to their deaths are still unknown. The Eastern Cape liquor board opened criminal charges against tavern owner, Vuyokazi  Ndevu. * eNCA's Aviwe Mtila reports. #SceneryPark youth and community hold a prayer session, candles in hand, outside #EnyobeniTavern where 21 teens mysteriously passed away. @eNCA #Enyobeni pic.twitter.com/xskP0triE7